<info>
<title>Welcome to XML Calabash (1.0)</title>
</info>

<important>
<para>These are not the web pages you are looking for. Go to the
<link xlink:href="/">home page</link> and follow the links for XML Calabash 3.x.
Or whatever seems most recent.</para>
<para>These are the archived pages for XML Calabash 1.x. As the release of XML
Calabash 3.0, a complete reimplementation for XProc 3.x, approaches (circa
October, 2024), it becomes less and less likely that there will be any more
updates here.</para>
<para>These pages are preserved out of a sense of obligation to the past. Or something.
I tried to fix all of the links, but I could have missed some.
</para>
</important>

<para><citetitle>XML Calabash</citetitle> is an implementation of
<citetitle xlink:href="http://www.w3.org/TR/xproc/">XProc:
An XML Pipeline Language</citetitle>.
</para>

<para>See the XML Calabash
<link xlink:href="http://github.com/ndw/xmlcalabash1">GitHub project
status page</link> for more details.</para>

<para>You can
<link xlink:href="https://github.com/ndw/xmlcalabash/releases/">download</link> Calabash and/or read
the
<link xlink:href="/docs/">documentation</link>. Calabash also ships with
the
<link xlink:href="http://www.oxygenxml.com/">&lt;oXygen/&gt; xml editor</link>
(as does <link xlink:href="http://www.saxonica.com/feature-matrix.html">Saxon-EE</link>
which includes support for validation with W3C XML Schema).</para>

<para>There is a <link xlink:href="docs/reference">reference guide</link>
to <citetitle>XML Calabash</citetitle>.</para>

